			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Last spring, when I was playing SW:ToR, I tried to upgrade the video drivers on my laptop in order for it to play at a decent frame rate.  At the time, the drivers were not digitally signed and I would have to hit F8 and tell Win 7 to ignore checking those and continue to boot.  At the time I found a batch file on a tech site that did this automatically, so it added a few seconds to the boot time, but I didn't have to do this manually every time.<br />
<br />
Now the drivers have been updated and are digitally signed and I'm wanting to remove that batch file so my bootup will speed up a bit.  I can't find the page I got the file from and I can't find where the batch file is to remove it.<br />
<br />
Anyone got an idea where to look to remove this?  I've been through MSConfig and don't see anything in there.</div>

