<br />
Thought it might be the power button; perhaps it severed. Unfortunately, the case is sealed and the wires are extremely hard to see, let alone get at. Unplugged the button and tried shorting the pins on the motherboard with a flathead screwdriver, but got nothing. Still not turning on. <br />
<br />
Before I flip out and try replacing the motherboard, does anyone have any other ideas I might pursue?</div>

